ttern in handler.ts that should be replicated?\n4. Are there any existing typed error extraction utilities in src/shared/errors/?\n5. What is the current state of src/shared/types.ts regarding SDK message types?\n\n**This is an internal refactor — no libraries needed.** Focus on:\n- Codebase patterns and conventions already established\n- Types already defined in the project\n- Verification patterns that should be used in plans\n- Common pitfalls when refactoring error handling in existing TypeScript codebases\n</additional_context>\n\n<downstream_consumer>\nYour RESEARCH.md will be loaded by gsd-planner which uses specific sections:\n- `## Standard Stack` — empty (no new deps), but document existing Zod version\n- `## Architecture Patterns` — Task structure follows these error-handling patterns\n- `## Don't Hand-Roll` — Nothing for this phase (no new deps)\n- `## Common Pitfalls` — Verification steps check for these\n- `## Code Examples` — Task actions reference these patterns from existing codebase\n\nBe prescriptive, not exploratory. Document existing patterns, don't recommend alternatives.\n</downstream_consumer>\n\n<output>\nWrite to: .planning/phases/C5-Error-Handling-Code-Quality/C5-RESEARCH.md\n</output>\n\n<quality_gate>\nBefore declaring complete, verify:\n- [ ] All 4 phase requirements addressed in research\n- [ ] Existing error handling patterns documented from source reads\n- [ ] SdkMessage type shape documented\n- [ ] Zod schema patterns documented for the Zod-schematized union\n- [ ] buildMinimalEnv pattern documented\n- [ ] Confidence levels assigned honestly (HIGH for verified source reads)\n- [ ] Section names match what plan-phase expects\n</quality_gate>",
